import {React, useState, useEffect} from 'react' import './Stats.css' function Stats() { const [github,setGithub] = useState([]) const [repos,setRepos] = useState([]) useEffect(() => { fetch('https://api.github.com/users/iampranavdhar') .then(response => response.json()) .then(result => setGithub(result)); fetch('https://api.github.com/users/iampranavdhar/repos') .then(response => response.json()) .then(repos => setRepos(repos)) },[]) return (

Stats

GitHub Followers

{github.followers}

GitHub Stars

{totalStars()}

GitHub Repos

{repos.length}

) } export default Stats
